In [9]:
# Number of columns per batch
batch_size = 20

# Total number of batches
num_batches = math.ceil(len(num_cols) / batch_size)

for i in range(num_batches):
    # Select columns for this batch
    batch_cols = num_cols[i*batch_size:(i+1)*batch_size]
    num_data_batch = data[batch_cols]

    # Plot boxplots for this batch
    plt.figure(figsize=(14,6))
    sns.boxplot(data=num_data_batch, orient="h")
    plt.title(f"Boxplots for Numerical Features (Batch {i+1})")
    plt.show()
In [10]:
def clip_outliers_iqr(x , columns , factor=1.5):
    x = x.copy()
    for col in columns:
        Q1=x[col].quantile(0.25)
        Q3=x[col].quantile(0.75)
        IQR =Q3 - Q1
        lower_bound = Q1 - factor * IQR
        upper_bound = Q3 + factor * IQR
        x[col] = x[col].clip(lower=lower_bound , upper=upper_bound)
    return x

x = clip_outliers_iqr(x , num_cols)

Feature Selection¶

In [25]:
select_kbest = SelectKBest(score_func=f_classif, k=50)

rf = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=150, random_state=42, n_jobs=-1)
select_rf = SelectFromModel(rf, max_features=50)

fs_pipeline = Pipeline([("select_kbest", select_kbest),("select_rf", select_rf)])

x_train_fs = fs_pipeline.fit_transform(x_train , y_train)
x_test_fs = fs_pipeline.transform(x_test)

In [31]:
# Feature names after ColumnTransformer
ohe = preprocessor.named_transformers_['cat']
ohe_feature_names = ohe.get_feature_names_out(cat_cols)
all_feature_names = np.concatenate([num_cols, ohe_feature_names])

# Step 1: Get KBest mask
kbest_mask = fs_pipeline.named_steps['select_kbest'].get_support()  # length = total features (e.g., 233)

# Step 2: Get KBest feature names
kbest_features = all_feature_names[kbest_mask]

# Step 3: Get RF mask
rf_mask = fs_pipeline.named_steps['select_rf'].get_support()  # length = number of features from KBest (e.g., 50)

# Step 4: Apply RF mask to KBest features
selected_features = kbest_features[rf_mask]

print("Selected Features:", selected_features)

In [27]:

y_test_pred  = lr.predict(x_test_fs)
